parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the digital instrument cluster can cause a lack of vital information to the driver, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The digital instrument cluster lights flicker
the digital instrument cluster goes completely blank
the issue only occurs upon cold start
the lights come back on when the vehicle warms up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Smoke comes out from the starter motor when the vehicle is started
the smoke disappears once the vehicle is moving for some time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended release of the seat belt buckle can lead to occupant ejection or failure to restrain, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle releases by itself
the seat belt will not retract
the seat belt is difficult to latch or unlatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
the vehicle does not stop or slows down unexpectedly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle crashes into another object or vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the airbag module is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Faulty Accelerator Pedal or Electronic Throttle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may accelerate suddenly and uncontrollably, even when the driver is attempting to brake or shift into park.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck to the floor
the vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when in park or neutral
sudden and unexpected acceleration
loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Glare from SUV and Pickup Truck Headlights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive glare from SUV and pickup truck headlights can cause temporary blindness, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Difficulty seeing the road ahead
temporary blindness
discomfort or pain in the eyes
inability to see pedestrians
other vehicles
or road obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improperly aimed headlights can cause glare, reduce visibility, and increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Glare from oncoming traffic
difficulty seeing the road ahead
temporary blindness
discomfort or pain in the eyes
inability to see pedestrians
other vehicles
or road obstacles.
